      "sha": "b78c7d242a988762c141384bc3d80309de2c805f",
      "filename": "changelog/releases/v1.0.2/notes.md",
      "status": "added",
      "additions": 9,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 9,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/test/blob/5a33fc78e7705e6e5fee74953f9e13a115b5b9e9/changelog%2Freleases%2Fv1.0.2%2Fnotes.md",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/test/raw/5a33fc78e7705e6e5fee74953f9e13a115b5b9e9/changelog%2Freleases%2Fv1.0.2%2Fnotes.md",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tenzir/test/contents/changelog%2Freleases%2Fv1.0.2%2Fnotes.md?ref=5a33fc78e7705e6e5fee74953f9e13a115b5b9e9",
      "patch": "@@ -0,0 +1,9 @@\n+This release improves the debugging experience by making the `--debug` flag automatically enable verbose output, so you see all test results when diagnosing failures.\n+\n+## \ud83d\udd27 Changes\n+\n+### Debug mode implies verbose output\n+\n+The `--debug` flag (or `TENZIR_TEST_DEBUG=1` environment variable) now automatically enables verbose output. When debugging test failures, you now see all test results (pass/skip/fail) instead of only failures, making it easier to diagnose issues. This provides more context without requiring users to pass both `--debug` and `--verbose` flags separately.\n+\n+*By @mavam and @claude in #9.*"
    },
